==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetrabasic
<hw>Tet`ra*bas"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetra-</ets> + <ets>basic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Capable of neutralizing four molecules of a monacid base; having
four hydrogen atoms capable of replacement by bases; quadribasic; --
said of certain acids; thus, normal silicic acid,
<chform>Si(OH)4</chform>, is a <xex>tetrabasic</xex> acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetraboric</ent>⟦br⟧
